column2: Building a bright future requires collective effort. In a family, both breadwinner and dependents play an important part in making the ends meet. It is no different for OFWs, but the added challenge is the long distance between them and their loved ones. Here are tips to help each member of the house take a responsible approach to money. üëõüëç bit.ly/ofwbudgetscopingwcovid #LifeGoals

column2: Here are short and quick pieces of advice to help you keep your investments on track. These tips will help you stay on top of your investments and financial goals during this time of health crisis and high market volatility. Browse the photos to know more. You can also see related tips here: bit.ly/protectinginvestments. #BrightTips

Go digital with Sun Life Asset Management! Find out how you can easily invest in mutual funds through the My Sun Life Client Portal and the Sun Life PH Mobile App. üì± Join our FREE webinar on Apr. 15 (Wednesday) at 2:00 PM. Register here: https://bit.ly/SLAMCICPMA

Everyone, including adults, experiences stress. It is natural to find yourself anxious given that there is a health crisis and we are trying to keep ourselves and our loved ones safe. Aside from the tips we shared through these photos, one remedy for stress is disconnecting with those that overwhelm and drain you whenever possible. Also, keep in mind that your version of productivity may be different from another person's. üòâ

column2: Happy #WorldHealthDay! We've been sharing workouts that you can do at home so you can keep yourself healthy and fit ‚Äî but remember that it is just as important to keep your mind in good shape. Practice mindfulness, give yourself the breaks that you deserve, give time to what you love, and do what aligns with your moral compass because these are the ways that you take care of your mental well-being. At the end of this pandemic and lockdown, make sure that you stay in agreement with yourself.
